cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classification tasks. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a new method for few-shot learning. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it aims to improve the performance of models in recognizing novel classes with few labeled data. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it mentions the use of cosine similarity, which is commonly used in text analysis. Finally, it involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes a prototypical network and a bias diminishing module to modify the prototypes.
